Countless homes have been destroyed following a massive storm and bad weather in KwaZulu-Natal. The storm began battering the province on the 30 December and since then the weather has been relentless with heavy downpours, hail and strong wind. eNCA's Mawande Kheswa has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Countless homes have been destroyed following a massive storm and bad weather in KwaZulu-Natal. The storm began battering the province on 30 December and since then the weather has been relentless with heavy downpours, hail, and strong wind. READ: Many left homeless after floods in North West Homes and infrastructure have been damaged and families displaced. One of the worst affected municipalities now wants its area declared a local disaster.